<div id=3D"what-are-temperature-conversion-formulas">
<div id=3D"circle" style=3D"background-color: rgb(225, 255, 246);"></div><h=
2>What are Temperature Conversion Formulas?</h2>
</div>
<p><strong>Temperature conversion formulas</strong> are defined as the conv=
ersion formulas for changing the value of temperature from one unit to anot=
her. They are various distinct <a href=3D"https://www.cuemath.com/measureme=
nt/temperature/">temperature</a> conversion methods. Kelvin, Celsius, and F=
ahrenheit are the most commonly used scales for temperature measurement. He=
re are the temperature conversion formulas:</p>
<ul>
<li>Celsius to Kelvin: K =3D C + 273.15</li>
<li>Kelvin to Celcius: C =3D K - 273.15</li>
<li>Fahrenheit to Celcius: C =3D (F-32) (5/9)</li>
<li>Celsius to Fahrenheit: F =3D C(9/5) + 32</li>
<li>Fahrenheit to Kelvin: K =3D (F-32) (5/9) + 273.15</li>
<li>Kelvin to Fahrenheit: F =3D (K-273.15) (9/5) + 32</li>
</ul>
<p><img alt=3D"Temperature Conversion Formulas" src=3D"https://d138zd1ktt9i=
qe.cloudfront.net/media/seo_landing_files/temperature-conversion-formulas-1=
623664596.png" style=3D"width: 400px;"></p>
<p>Before learning the temperature conversion formulas, let us recall the u=
nits of temperature in detail.</p>
<div id=3D"units-of-temperature">
<div id=3D"circle" style=3D"background-color: rgb(225, 255, 246);"></div><h=
2>Units of Temperature</h2>
</div>
<p>Different units can be used to record the temperature. The three differe=
nt units used for measuring temperature are Celsius (=C2=B0C) Fahrenheit (=
=C2=B0F), and Kelvin (K). Kelvin is the SI unit of measuring temperature, w=
hereas Fahrenheit and Celsius are commonly used scales.</p>
<h3>Celsius</h3>
<p>Celsius scale was Invented in 1742 by Swedish astronomer Anders Celsius =
and hence named after him. Celsius, also called centigrade, is based on the=
 freezing point of water which is 0=C2=B0, and the boiling point of water w=
hich is 100=C2=B0 The temperature in celsius is represented with =C2=B0C. N=
ormal human body temperature is 37=C2=B0C.</p>
<p><img alt=3D"celsius scale" src=3D"https://d138zd1ktt9iqe.cloudfront.net/=
media/seo_landing_files/temperature-converter-image-1-1614263746.png" style=
=3D"width: 400px;"></p>
<h3>Fahrenheit</h3>
<p>The Fahrenheit scale is a temperature scale developed by Daniel Gabriel =
Fahrenheit and hence named after him. This scale has the boiling point of w=
ater at 212=C2=B0 F and the freezing point at 32=C2=B0 F. The temperature i=
n Fahrenheit is represented with =C2=B0F. The normal human body temperature=
 is 98.6=C2=B0F.</p>
<p><img alt=3D"fahrenheit scale " src=3D"https://d138zd1ktt9iqe.cloudfront.=
net/media/seo_landing_files/temperature-converter-image-2-1614263776.png" s=
tyle=3D"width: 400px;"></p>
<h3>Kelvin</h3>
<p>Kelvin is the SI unit of temperature. The unit symbol is K. It is named =
after the physicist William Thomson, 1<sup>st</sup> Baron Kelvin (1824=E2=
=80=931907). Here the degree symbol =C2=B0 is not used to represent the tem=
perature, unlike in Celsius or Fahrenheit.</p>
<p><img alt=3D"kelvin thermometer" src=3D"https://d138zd1ktt9iqe.cloudfront=
.net/media/seo_landing_files/temperature-converter-image-3-1614263809.png" =
style=3D"width: 400px;"></p>
<div id=3D"temperature-conversion-formulas-between-celsius-and-kelvin">
<div id=3D"circle" style=3D"background-color: rgb(225, 255, 246);"></div><h=
2>Temperature Conversion Formulas Between Celsius and Kelvin</h2>
</div>
<p>Conversion of temperature between Celsius and Kelvin is done using the f=
ollowing formulas:</p>
<ul>
<li>The temperature conversion formula from <a href=3D"https://www.cuemath.=
com/celsius-to-kelvin-formula/">Celsius to Kelvin</a> is:<br>
	K =3D C + 273.15</li>
<li>The temperature conversion formula from Kelvin to Celcius is:<br>
	C =3D K =E2=88=92 273.15</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Example: </strong>Convert 16=C2=B0C into Kelvin.</p>
<p><strong>Solution: </strong></p>
<p>C =3D 16=C2=B0C (Given). Using the <a href=3D"https://www.cuemath.com/ce=
lsius-to-kelvin-formula/">Celsius to Kelvin conversion formula</a>,</p>
<p>K =3D C + 273.15</p>
<p>=3D 16 + 273.15</p>
<p>=3D 289.15 K</p>
<p>Therefore, 16=C2=B0C is equivalent to 289.15 K.</p>
