2>Temperature Conversion Formulas Between Fahrenheit and Celsius</h2>
</div>
<p>Conversion of temperature between Fahrenheit and Celsius is done using t=
he following formulas:</p>
<ul>
<li>The temperature conversion formula from <a href=3D"https://www.cuemath.=
com/fahrenheit-to-celsius-formula/">Fahrenheit to Celsius</a> is:<br>
	C =3D (F =E2=88=92 32) =C3=97 5/9</li>
<li>The temperature conversion formula from <a href=3D"https://www.cuemath.=
com/c-to-f-formula/">Celsius to Fahrenheit</a>&nbsp;is:<br>
	F =3D C(9/5) + 32</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Example:</strong> What is 115=C2=B0F on the Celsius scale?</p>
<p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
<p>F =3D 115=C2=B0F.</p>
<p>Using Fahrenheit to Celsius conversion formula,</p>
<p>C =3D (F =E2=88=92 32) =C3=97 5/9</p>
<p>=3D (115 =E2=88=92 32)<strong> </strong>=C3=97<strong> </strong>(5/9)</p=
>
<p>=3D 46.11=C2=B0F<strong> </strong></p>
<p>Therefore,<strong> </strong>115=C2=B0F is 46.11=C2=B0C on the centigrade=
 scale.</p>
<div id=3D"temperature-conversion-formulas-between-fahrenheit-and-kelvin">
<div id=3D"circle" style=3D"background-color: rgb(225, 255, 246);"></div><h=
2>Temperature Conversion Formulas Between Fahrenheit and Kelvin</h2>
</div>
<p>Conversion of temperature between Fahrenheit and Kelvin is done using th=
e following formulas:</p>
<ul>
<li>The temperature conversion formula from <a href=3D"https://www.cuemath.=
com/fahrenheit-to-kelvin-formula/">Fahrenheit to Kelvin</a> is:<br>
	K =3D (F =E2=88=92 32) =C3=97 5/9 + 273.15</li>
<li>The temperature conversion formula from Kelvin to Fahrenheit is:<br>
	F =3D (K =E2=80=93 273.15) =C3=97 9/5 + 32</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Example:</strong> Convert 100 degrees Fahrenheit to Kelvin.</p>
<p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
<p>Temperature in Fahrenheit, F =3D 100 F(Given). Using<a href=3D"https://w=
ww.cuemath.com/fahrenheit-to-kelvin-formula/"> Fahrenheit to Kelvin Formula=
</a>,</p>
<p>K<sub> </sub>=3D (F =E2=88=92 32) =C3=97 5/9 + 273.15</p>
<p>=3D(100 =E2=88=92 32) =C3=97 5/9 + 273.15</p>
<p>=3D 310.93 K</p>
<p>Therefore, 100 degree Fahrenheit =3D 310.93 K</p>
