<div>
<p><strong>Example 1:</strong> We know that one degree Celsius is equal to =
273.15 Kelvin. Calculate 30=C2=B0C in Kelvin.</p>
<p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
<p>To find: Convert 30=C2=B0C in Kelvin.</p>
<p>Given,</p>
<p>One-degree Celsius is equal to 273.15 Kelvin.</p>
<p>Using temperature conversion formulas,</p>
<p>Kelvin (K) =3D Celsius(C) + 273.15</p>
<p>Putting the value:</p>
<p>K =3D 30 + 273.15 K =3D 303.15 K=E2=80=89</p>
<p>=3D 303.15 K</p>
<p><strong>Answer:</strong> 30=C2=B0C in Kelvin is 303.15 K</p>
</div>
</li>
<li class=3D"cue-slide" id=3D"slide-111">
<div>
<p><strong>Example 2:</strong> The body temperature is generally 98.6=C2=BA=
F. Find the body temperature in Celsius using temperature conversion formul=
as.</p>
<p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
<p>To find: The body temperature in Celsius.</p>
<p>Given,</p>
<p>The body temperature on the Celcius scale is 98.6=C2=BAF.</p>
<p>The formula to convert Fahrenheit to Celsius is,</p>
<p>C =3D (F =E2=88=92 32) =C3=97 5/9</p>
<p>On putting the value, we get</p>
<p>C =3D (98.6 =E2=88=92 32) =C3=97 5/9</p>
<p>=3D 37=C2=B0C</p>
<p><strong>Answer:</strong> The body temperature in Celsius is 37=C2=B0C.</=
p>
</div>
</li>
<li class=3D"cue-slide" id=3D"slide-112">
<div>
