<p>We apply temperature conversion formulas.</p>
<p>Using Kelvin to Celsius conversion formula<br>
	C =3D K =E2=80=93 273.15<br>
	=3D 220 =E2=80=93 273.15<br>
	=3D -53.15=C2=B0C</p>
<p>Using Kelvin to Fahrenheit conversion formula<br>
	F =3D (K =E2=80=93 273.15) =C3=97 9/5 + 32<br>
	=3D (220 =E2=80=93 273.15) =C3=97 9/5 + 32<br>
	=3D -53.15 =C3=97 9/5 + 32 =3D -95.67 + 32 =3D -63.67=C2=B0F</p>
<p><strong>Answer:</strong> 220K in Celsius is -53.15=C2=B0C and Fahrenheit=
 is -63.67=C2=B0F.</p>
</div>
</li>
